    <article class="prose-editorial cs-body" set:html={`<h3>Educational Case Study Disclosure<br /><br /></h3><p>This case study is hypothetical and for educational purposes only. Scenarios, borrower profiles, loan terms, interest rates, and APRs are illustrative examples and do not represent current offers or guaranteed terms.</p><p>If specific loan terms (e.g., down payment %, payment amount, rate/APR, points, or repayment period) appear in this article, required disclosures will be shown immediately next to those terms per Regulation Z.</p><p><strong>For specific details including down payment incentives, closing cost incentives, interest rate details, closing cost breakdowns, payment calculations, cash-to-close estimates, or an official Loan Estimate, it is highly recommended you <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">schedule a meeting with one of our licensed mortgage advisors</a>.</strong></p><p><strong>Learn more:</strong></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/24/">Reg Z – Advertising (§1026.24)</a> - CFPB official regulation</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1026/subpart-C/section-1026.24">Reg Z Full Text</a> - Electronic Code of Federal Regulations</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/interp-24/">Official Interpretations to §1026.24</a> - CFPB interpretations</li><li><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-12/chapter-X/part-1014">MAP Rule (Reg N), 12 CFR Part 1014</a> - Mortgage advertising rules</li><li><a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/">NMLS Consumer Access</a> - Verify licensure</li></ul><p>Actual loan terms vary by credit profile, property, occupancy, location, market conditions, and lender guidelines. For current options tailored to you, schedule a consultation or apply online.</p><p>Ready to explore your options? <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor.</p>		
					<h2>How This Asset-Based Loan Refinance Reduced Monthly Payments Without Income Verification</h2>				
		<p>Robert K., a 67-year-old retired corporate executive based in Naples, had built substantial wealth during his 35-year career in pharmaceutical leadership. After retiring three years earlier, Robert maintained a significant portfolio of liquid assets including retirement accounts, stock holdings, bonds, and diversified investments—providing comfortable income through dividends, distributions, and strategic withdrawals managed by his experienced wealth advisor.</p><p>Robert owned his primary residence with substantial equity built over years of steady appreciation, but his existing mortgage carried a higher interest rate from when he purchased the home pre-retirement during a period of elevated rates. With current market rates significantly lower than his existing rate, Robert wanted to refinance to reduce his monthly payment and improve his overall financial efficiency during retirement. The monthly savings would provide additional flexibility for travel, family gifts, and charitable giving—all important priorities in his retirement years.</p><p>However, Robert's income situation created substantial challenges with traditional refinance lenders. He no longer received W-2 income from employment. His tax returns showed relatively modest income because he strategically managed withdrawals from retirement accounts to minimize tax liability according to his wealth advisor's sophisticated tax-efficiency strategy. His actual financial capacity—demonstrated powerfully through substantial liquid assets—didn't translate well into traditional income documentation required by conventional lenders.</p><p>Robert needed a refinance solution that recognized his strong financial position without requiring employment income verification or complex tax return analysis that didn't reflect his true financial strength.</p><p><b>Facing similar challenges?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to explore your options.</p><h2><b>The Challenge: Why Traditional Refinance Lenders Required Extensive Documentation</b></h2><p>Robert approached two conventional refinance lenders confident that his excellent credit, perfect payment history, and substantial financial resources would make approval straightforward. He wanted a simple rate-and-term refinance—no cash out, no increase in loan amount, just better terms at current lower rates to reduce monthly payments.</p><p>Both lenders immediately requested extensive income documentation that seemed disconnected from his actual financial situation.</p><h3><b>What Income Documentation Did Traditional Lenders Demand from a Retiree?</b></h3><p>Traditional refinance lenders requested two years of complete tax returns with all schedules, Social Security benefit statements, pension documentation (though Robert had none), retirement account distribution letters explaining withdrawal amounts, investment income verification from brokerage statements, and detailed written explanations of his retirement cash flow management strategy. The complexity of documenting retirement income—including required minimum distributions, strategic tax-efficient withdrawals, dividend payments from various holdings, and Social Security benefits—created substantial underwriting challenges and confusion.</p><p>"I felt frustrated having to explain that I don't have traditional employment income because I'm retired," Robert explained. "I have substantial liquid assets—diversified investment portfolios worth significantly more than my home and mortgage balance combined. But lenders kept asking for income documentation that didn't really apply to my situation. I'm not employed. I'm retired and living comfortably off my investments, exactly as I planned during decades of career success."</p><h3><b>Why Couldn't Traditional Lenders Understand Robert's Financial Strength?</b></h3><p>The income verification challenge was particularly frustrating because Robert's financial position was exceptionally strong by any reasonable measure. His liquid asset portfolio value far exceeded his remaining mortgage balance—he could pay off the mortgage entirely with cash if he chose. He'd never missed a payment in his life. His credit score was excellent. He had substantial cash reserves beyond his investment portfolio. But traditional lenders struggled to fit his retirement income structure into their standard underwriting boxes designed around employment income.</p><p>"Traditional lenders wanted me to document and verify every income stream—Social Security, IRA withdrawals, taxable brokerage account distributions, tax-exempt municipal bond interest," Robert said. "They needed letters from my wealth advisor explaining my withdrawal strategy, projections of future distributions based on portfolio performance assumptions, and detailed tax return analysis going back multiple years. The documentation burden was overwhelming and completely unnecessary for what should have been a straightforward refinance based on my obvious financial capacity."</p><h3><b>What Opportunity Cost Did Robert Face While Waiting?</b></h3><p>The timing frustration added another dimension. Current market rates were significantly lower than Robert's existing mortgage rate from several years earlier, creating substantial potential monthly savings. Every month he waited for traditional refinance approval was money unnecessarily lost—monthly savings he could be enjoying for travel with his wife, supporting his grandchildren's education, or increasing charitable contributions to causes important to him in retirement.</p><p>Additionally, Robert didn't want to provide extensive personal financial details to lenders who couldn't quickly understand or properly appreciate his retirement financial structure. His wealth advisor had crafted a sophisticated withdrawal strategy carefully optimizing tax efficiency by drawing from various account types strategically, and Robert felt that conventional lenders lacked the expertise to properly evaluate retirement income structures.</p><p><b>Experiencing similar frustration with traditional lending requirements?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> to discuss alternative solutions.</p><h2><b>The Discovery: How Robert Found Asset-Based Refinancing</b></h2><p>During a quarterly wealth management review, Robert mentioned his refinance frustrations and the documentation barriers he was facing to his financial advisor. The advisor immediately suggested exploring<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/"> asset-based refinance</a> programs designed specifically for retired individuals and high-net-worth clients with substantial liquid assets. The advisor explained that these programs qualify borrowers based on investment portfolio values rather than traditional income documentation.</p><h3><b>What Made Robert Skeptical About Alternative Refinancing Options?</b></h3><p>Intrigued but initially skeptical, Robert scheduled a consultation with a loan advisor specializing in asset-based lending for retirees and high-net-worth borrowers. He doubted that any lender would refinance his mortgage without extensive income verification—every lender he'd ever worked with seemed rigidly focused on income documentation. But his wealth advisor's strong recommendation gave him confidence to explore the option.</p><h3><b>How Do Asset-Based Refinance Lenders Evaluate Retirees Differently?</b></h3><p>During the consultation, the advisor explained how asset-based refinancing works fundamentally differently than traditional mortgages. Instead of analyzing tax returns and income streams, asset-based refinance lenders evaluate liquid asset portfolios—retirement accounts, stock holdings, bonds, mutual funds, and other investment accounts. The loan qualification is based on total portfolio value and asset quality rather than employment income or retirement distribution amounts.</p><p>"That conversation completely shifted my perspective on refinancing," Robert said. "The advisor explained that with my substantial investment portfolio, I could qualify for refinancing without providing tax returns, Social Security statements, or detailed income explanations that traditional lenders demanded. The focus would be purely on my liquid assets—which were more than sufficient to support the mortgage refinance comfortably. It made perfect sense for retirees like me who have significant wealth but complex income structures on paper."</p><h3><b>What Was Robert's "Aha Moment" About This Approach?</b></h3><p>The advisor also explained that asset-based refinancing particularly benefits retirees who have significant wealth accumulated in investment accounts but complex or modest income showing on tax documents. Many retirees strategically manage withdrawals to minimize taxes as part of sophisticated wealth preservation strategies, making their tax returns poor representations of their actual financial capacity. Asset-based refinance lenders recognize this retirement financial reality and focus on what truly matters—the total financial resources available to support obligations.</p><p>Robert learned that the approval process would be dramatically streamlined compared to traditional refinancing. No need to document every income stream with verification letters. No complex retirement income calculations projecting future distributions. No extensive tax return analysis trying to fit retirement withdrawals into employment income frameworks. Just straightforward portfolio verification and credit review—simple, fast, and focused on his actual financial strength.</p><h2><b>The Solution: Asset-Based Loan Refinance Approval Process</b></h2><p>Robert worked closely with his loan advisor to assemble the required documentation for his asset-based loan refinance application. The process focused entirely on his liquid asset portfolio rather than income verification, dramatically simplifying requirements and accelerating the timeline substantially.</p><h3><b>What Documentation Did Robert Provide for His Refinance?</b></h3><p><b>Documentation provided:</b></p><ul><li>Comprehensive investment account statements showing substantial portfolio value across multiple accounts</li><li>Detailed asset portfolio breakdown including retirement accounts, stocks, bonds, mutual funds, and cash holdings</li><li>Account statements from wealth management firm and multiple brokerage accounts</li><li>Excellent credit score with perfect mortgage payment history over many years</li><li>Current mortgage balance and home value documentation showing substantial equity position</li><li>Strong cash reserves for closing costs and future mortgage payments</li><li>Minimal income documentation—no tax returns or detailed income verification required</li><li>No cash-out needed—straightforward rate-and-term refinance for better terms</li></ul><h3><b>How Long Did Robert's Asset-Based Refinance Take?</b></h3><p><b>The approval timeline:</b></p><ol><li><b>Initial consultation (Day 1)</b> — Discussed refinance goals and asset-based qualification approach</li><li><b>Asset portfolio review (Days 1-3)</b> — Analyzed total liquid asset values and portfolio composition</li><li><b>Pre-qualification confirmed (Day 4)</b> — Verified eligibility for refinance based on substantial assets</li><li><b>Document submission (Days 5-7)</b> — Uploaded investment account statements through secure portal</li><li><b>Asset verification (Days 8-11)</b> — Asset-based refinance lender verified portfolio values with custodians</li><li><b>Credit review (Days 12-13)</b> — Verified excellent credit score and perfect payment history</li><li><b>Property appraisal ordered (Day 14)</b> — Scheduled appraisal to confirm current home value</li><li><b>Appraisal completed (Day 19)</b> — Home appraised at favorable value</li><li><b>Underwriting approval (Day 21)</b> — Approved for refinance based on asset portfolio strength</li><li><b>Final review (Days 22-24)</b> — Completed remaining documentation</li><li><b>Clear to close (Day 25)</b> — Final approval granted</li><li><b>Closing scheduled (Day 28)</b> — Closed on refinance in under 30 days</li></ol><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Refinance Lenders Evaluate Robert's Financial Capacity?</b></h3><p>The asset-based refinance lender evaluated Robert's substantial liquid investment portfolio and assessed total financial resources rather than monthly income streams. They determined that his portfolio provided more than sufficient financial capacity to support the refinanced mortgage comfortably, with substantial cushion beyond what any debt-to-income ratio would show.</p><p>This approach recognized the fundamental reality that many retirees have wealth structured in investments rather than employment income, and that portfolio value demonstrates financial capacity more reliably than retirement income documentation for high-net-worth individuals.</p><h3><b>What Made Robert's Application Particularly Strong?</b></h3><p>Several factors strengthened Robert's asset-based refinance application. His excellent credit score demonstrated lifelong financial responsibility. His perfect mortgage payment history showed he understood obligations and honored commitments consistently. His diversified portfolio across multiple asset classes showed sophisticated wealth management. His substantial home equity reduced lender risk. And his long-term relationship with a reputable wealth management firm added credibility.</p><p>The combination positioned Robert as an exceptionally low-risk borrower using asset-based qualification criteria.</p><p><b>Ready to refinance and reduce your monthly payments?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/refinance-or-heloc-inquiry/"> Submit a refinance inquiry</a> to compare your options.</p><h2><b>The Results: How Did Asset-Based Refinancing Improve Robert's Retirement Financial Position?</b></h2><p>Robert closed on his refinance in under 30 days after submitting his initial application—capturing favorable market rates and immediately beginning to enjoy monthly savings. The rate-and-term refinance lowered his interest rate significantly, reduced his monthly payment substantially, and positioned him to save considerable cumulative interest over his remaining mortgage term.</p><h3><b>What Were the Final Terms of Robert's Refinance?</b></h3><p><b>Final loan outcome:</b></p><ul><li>Approved refinance matched existing mortgage balance—pure rate-and-term improvement</li><li>Significantly lower interest rate compared to previous mortgage</li><li>Favorable long-term fixed-rate structure</li><li>Substantially reduced monthly payment</li><li>Timeline: Under 30 days from application to closing</li><li>Considerable projected cumulative interest savings</li><li>Portfolio remained fully invested—no liquidation required</li><li>No complex income verification required</li></ul><h3><b>How Did Asset-Based Qualification Compare to Traditional Lending?</b></h3><p><b>Traditional refinance lender vs. asset-based refinance lender comparison:</b></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><b>Qualification Factor</b></p></td><td><p><b>Traditional Lender</b></p></td><td><p><b>Asset-Based Refinance Lender</b></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Primary qualification basis</b></p></td><td><p>Retirement income documentation</p></td><td><p>Liquid investment portfolio value</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Tax returns required</b></p></td><td><p>Two years with all schedules</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Income verification complexity</b></p></td><td><p>Extensive documentation</p></td><td><p>Minimal documentation</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Social Security statements</b></p></td><td><p>Required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>IRA distribution letters</b></p></td><td><p>Required</p></td><td><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Portfolio consideration</b></p></td><td><p>Secondary or ignored</p></td><td><p>Primary qualification factor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Approval timeline</b></p></td><td><p>Extended process</p></td><td><p>Streamlined (under 30 days)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Refinance goal</b></p></td><td><p>BLOCKED ❌</p></td><td><p>ACHIEVED ✅</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><b>Monthly savings</b></p></td><td><p>Impossible</p></td><td><p>Substantial reduction ✅</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3><b>What Immediate Benefits Did Robert Experience?</b></h3><p>"Without asset-based refinancing, I'd still be paying my old higher rate and losing money every month unnecessarily," Robert explained. "Traditional lenders wanted extensive income documentation that didn't reflect my financial reality. Asset-based lending recognized what actually mattered—my substantial investment portfolio demonstrating clear financial capacity. The process was straightforward, fast, and focused on relevant factors."</p><p>The monthly payment reduction provided immediate cash flow relief that Robert redirected toward priorities important in retirement. He increased his monthly charitable giving to causes he cared about. He budgeted more generously for travel with his wife to destinations they'd postponed. He increased financial support for his grandchildren's education. The refinance created meaningful financial flexibility while maintaining his comfortable lifestyle.</p><h3><b>How Does This Refinance Fit Into Robert's Retirement Strategy?</b></h3><p>Robert views this refinance as smart financial stewardship during retirement—reducing fixed housing costs to improve overall retirement budget flexibility and preserve wealth for legacy planning. Lower monthly payments improve his monthly cash flow without requiring higher portfolio withdrawals. Substantial long-term cumulative interest savings preserve more wealth for family inheritance and charitable bequests.</p><p>"For retirees with substantial portfolios, asset-based refinancing makes perfect sense," Robert added. "We've spent decades building investment wealth specifically to support retirement comfortably. Asset-based refinance lenders recognize that accumulated wealth and use it appropriately for qualification—exactly as they should. Traditional lenders get stuck trying to fit retirement income into employment income boxes, which simply doesn't work well for our financial structures."</p><h3><b>What Future Flexibility Has Robert Gained?</b></h3><p>Robert's established relationship with asset-based lenders provides future financial flexibility. If rates drop further, he knows he can potentially refinance again efficiently. If he wants to access equity for a vacation property, helping adult children purchase homes, or other goals, he understands that<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/"> cash-out refinancing</a> or a<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/"> HELOC</a> would be available options—all working with his retirement financial structure rather than against it.</p><p><b>Ready to get started on your refinance?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> Get approved</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a call</a> to discuss your retirement financial situation.</p><h2><b>Exploring Other Asset-Based Loan Options?</b></h2><p>While Robert used an asset-based loan for rate-and-term refinancing, asset-based financing works for multiple scenarios:</p><ul><li><b>Need to purchase property?</b> See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-purchase"> investment banker used asset-based loan purchase for luxury waterfront home</a> with quick approval</li><li><b>Want to access equity?</b> See how an<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/"> entrepreneur used asset-based cash-out refinance for business capital</a> while preserving investments</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> to find success stories matching your financial situation</li></ul><h2><b>Key Takeaways for Retired and High-Net-Worth Borrowers</b></h2><h3><b>What Can Retirees and Portfolio Investors Learn from This Refinance Success?</b></h3><ul><li><b>Asset-based loan refinancing qualifies borrowers based on liquid portfolio values, not traditional income</b>—perfect for retirees with substantial investments but complex income structures that don't translate well to traditional underwriting. Portfolio value demonstrates financial capacity more accurately than retirement distribution documentation (<a href="https://www.irs.gov/publications/p575">IRS retirement income guidelines</a>)<br /><br /></li><li><b>Simplified documentation eliminates frustrating income verification requirements</b>—no tax returns, no Social Security statements, no retirement account distribution letters, no complex income stream analysis needed. Focus purely on demonstrable financial resources<br /><br /></li><li><b>Retirees don't need to alter sophisticated tax-efficient withdrawal strategies to qualify</b>—asset-based refinance lenders work with your wealth management approach, not against it. Continue optimizing tax efficiency without sacrificing refinancing access (<a href="https://www.sec.gov/investor">SEC retirement account regulations</a>)<br /><br /></li><li><b>Substantial portfolio values demonstrate financial capacity more accurately than income documentation</b>—many retirees have wealth far exceeding what monthly income documents would suggest. Asset-based lenders recognize this retirement financial reality<br /><br /></li><li><b>Rate-and-term refinancing can significantly reduce monthly housing costs in retirement</b>—strategic refinancing during favorable rate environments improves retirement budget flexibility and preserves wealth for legacy goals<br /><br /></li><li><b>Excellent credit and perfect payment history remain important even with asset-based qualification</b>—strong credit profile helped Robert secure competitive pricing despite alternative qualification method<br /><br /></li></ul><p><b>Have questions about asset-based refinancing for retirees?</b><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Schedule a call</a> with a loan advisor experienced in retirement financing.</p><h2><b>Alternative Loan Programs for Retired Borrowers</b></h2><p>If an asset-based loan refinance isn't the perfect fit for your situation, consider these alternative financing options:</p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/bank-statement-loan/">Bank Statement Loan</a> – Refinance using bank deposits for retirees with income from multiple sources</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/non-qm-loan/">Non-QM Loan</a> – Flexible qualification options for unique retirement income situations</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/reverse-mortgage/">Reverse Mortgage</a> – Access home equity without monthly payments (age 62+)</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/heloc/">HELOC</a> – Access equity without refinancing first mortgage if you want to preserve current rate</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/home-equity-loan/">Home Equity Loan</a> – Fixed-rate second lien to access equity while keeping first mortgage intact</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/p-and-l-loan/">P&amp;L Loan (Profit and Loss)</a> – For retirees with continuing business or consulting income</li></ul><p><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/">Explore all loan programs</a> to find your best option.</p><p>Want to explore your retirement financing strategy?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/"> Take our discovery quiz</a> to clarify your goals.</p><h2><b>Helpful Asset-Based Loan Refinance Resources</b></h2><p><b>Learn more about this loan program:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/asset-based-loan/">Complete Asset-Based Loan Guide</a> – Detailed requirements and qualification guidelines for portfolio-based refinancing</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/asset-based-loan-calculator">Asset-Based Loan Calculator</a> – Estimate potential savings based on your portfolio value</li></ul><p><b>Similar success stories:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-purchase">How an investment banker purchased luxury home with asset-based loan</a> – Quick-close purchase success</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/asset-based-loan-cash-out-refinance/">Entrepreneur's asset-based cash-out refinance</a> – Accessing equity for business investment</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/case-studies/">View all case studies</a> – Browse by financial situation and goals</li></ul><p><b>External authoritative resources:</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.irs.gov/publications/p575">IRS Retirement Income Guidelines</a> – Understanding retirement income structures and tax implications</li><li><a href="https://www.sec.gov/investor">SEC Retirement Account Regulations</a> – Investment account types and retirement planning guidance</li><li><a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/ask-cfpb/what-is-a-reverse-mortgage-en-224/">CFPB Reverse Mortgage Information</a> – Comparing refinance options for retirees</li></ul><p><b>Ready to get started?</b></p><ul><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/">Apply online</a> – Start your refinance application today</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">Schedule a consultation</a> – Discuss your portfolio and retirement goals with experienced advisors</li><li><a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/discovery-quiz/">Take the discovery quiz</a> – Deep dive into your retirement financial strategy</li></ul><p>Need local expertise?<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/get-a-local-introduction/"> Get introduced to trusted partners</a> including wealth advisors and retirement planning specialists.</p><p><b>Disclosure:</b> <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/nexa-mortgage-partnership/"  data-wpil-monitor-id="314">NEXA Mortgage</a>, LLC dba Stairway Mortgage — NMLS #1660690 • Equal Housing Lender. Applications are handled by state-licensed Mortgage Loan Originators; you will be matched with an MLO licensed in your state. Not all products are available in all states. See our<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/licenses-disclosures"> Licenses &amp; Disclosures</a> page for state-specific information. This case study is for educational and illustrative purposes only. Scenarios, borrowers, and loan terms may be hypothetical and are used to demonstrate potential financing solutions. Not a commitment to lend. All loans are subject to credit approval, program availability, and underwriting guidelines. Interest rates, fees, loan amounts, and other terms are examples and do not represent current offers or market rates. Actual terms vary by applicant profile, property, market conditions, and lender guidelines, and may change without notice. Asset-based lending involves pledging liquid assets as collateral or qualification basis; specific lender requirements vary regarding asset types, liquidity, and portfolio composition. For current terms specific to your situation, please<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> schedule a consultation</a> or<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/same-day-approval/"> apply online</a>. NMLS Consumer Access:<a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/"> https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org/</a></p>		
